{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "More funding to enforce traffic offences committed by cycle/scooter users",
        "additional_details": "We want the Government to take notice and act in accordance with the law, as we believe is not always being enforced by the Police. We believe this would lead to greater accountability for those riding on pavements amongst pedestrians, which are meant to be protected public spaces for pedestrians.",
        "background": "We want the government to provide more funding for the enforcement of traffic offences committed by cyclists and those riding e-scooters. This should include riding on pavements in protected and public spaces. ",
